# PS4 Baikal Kernel 6.x Patch Series
#
# Apply order: low number first. Within a directory, files apply
# alphabetically (0001-..., 0002-..., etc.).
#
# Source:
#   - Bulk patches extracted from crashniels/linux ps4-linux-6.15.y-baikal
#     (HEAD b3b6b1e4f) on top of vanilla v6.15.4 (e60eb4415).
#     crashniels has already done the heavy 5.4 → 6.15 forward-port,
#     including Liverpool support in radeon, amdkfd quirks, the MSI
#     subsystem refactor, and the iommu directory move.
#   - feeRnt's xhci-aeolia Baikal shutdown fix
#     (b0969f7d101f, on x_exp__6.15.4-baikal-crashniels).
#   - One local fix for the bpcie-icc void-pointer bug.
#
# Notable gaps vs the 5.4-baikal stack:
#   - MT7668 (mt76x8) vendor WiFi/BT driver is NOT yet ported. Boot the
#     kernel without WiFi first; mt7668 is tracked in 9000-todo/.
#
# Generator: scripts/generate-6.x-patches.sh
#
# To temporarily disable a patch, comment its line.

