# v40: THE ACTUAL ROOT CAUSE FIX for 6.x HDMI. PS4 has null_legacy_pic
# so early_irq_init allocates 0 legacy descs. ACPI request_irq(9, ...)
# for SCI fails (-EINVAL) because irq_to_desc(9)=NULL. Cascade:
# SCI install fails -> acpi_terminate -> mutex delete -> ATOM BIOS
# returns 0 -> amdgpu PLL garbage -> blank HDMI.
# Pre-allocate IRQ 9 desc with dummy_irq_chip in arch_initcall.
0100-x86-platform/0002-x86-ps4-allocate-irq9-desc-for-acpi-sci.patch

# === 0150: ACPI OSL fixes (PS4-specific)
# v35: Revert SCI install from request_threaded_irq to request_irq.
# This is the ROOT CAUSE of the HDMI display being broken in 6.x.
# 6.x's IRQF_ONESHOT shared-add gets rejected on PS4 IRQ9 -> ACPI mutex
# init incomplete -> ATOM BIOS broken -> amdgpu PLL programming dead.
0150-acpi/0001-acpi-osl-ps4-revert-sci-to-request-irq.patch

